<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	  mise entitlements — Developer ID (direct distribution), NOT Mac App Store.

	  The App Sandbox is intentionally DISABLED. mise is distributed directly
	  via a notarized Developer ID build (not the MAS), so we do not require the
	  sandbox. Leaving it off gives the app unrestricted filesystem and network
	  access (e.g. reading user-chosen library exports, talking to TMDB / the
	  network) without having to enumerate sandbox temporary-exception
	  entitlements.

	  Hardened Runtime IS enabled (see ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME in project.yml),
	  which is required for notarization. The entitlements below are the
	  hardened-runtime-compatible set: none of the JIT / dyld / library-loading
	  exceptions are turned on, because mise does not need them. Add them only
	  if a future dependency genuinely requires it.

	  IF YOU EVER ADOPT THE SANDBOX (e.g. to ship on the Mac App Store), add:
	    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>            <true/>
	    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>         <true/>   (outbound TMDB / network)
	    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-only</key> <true/>  (importing a Letterboxd export)
	  …and re-test, since the sandbox will then restrict filesystem access.
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
